edu.gatech.mbse.transformations.sysml2milp.model

Class ProcessConstraintGenerator

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.gatech.mbse.transformations.sysml2milp.model.ProcessConstraintGenerator

  • public class ProcessConstraintGenerator
extends java.lang.Object
    Class containing functions that parse the internal process model and generate constraints and variables to calculate the throughput, and to ensure adherence to precedence constraints and keep track of timing (e.g., also to calculate productionTime).
    Version:
    0.1
    Author:
    Sebastian

      • generateVariables

        public java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.String> generateVariables(Process process,
                                                      MILPModel2TextUtils milpGen)
        Generates all timing variables relevant for a particular process.

        Genreates variable declarations for the relative start and end time, as well as the duration.

        Parameters:
        process - The process to generate timing variables for.
        milpGen - The MILP code generation object.
        Returns:
        A list of variable declarations in the target MILP syntax.

      • generateTimingConstraints

        public java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.String> generateTimingConstraints(Process process)
        Computes and returns a set of timing-related constraints.

        These constraints ensure precedence: e.g., end >= start + duration. Also generated are constraints relevant to parallel process branches where the execution time of n parallel branches is determined by the maximum time any of the n branches takes.

        Parameters:
        process - The process to generate these constraints for
        Returns:
        An ordered list of constraints.

      • generateResourceSharingConstraints

        Returns:
        A list of constraints.

      • generateUtilizationVariables

        public java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.String> generateUtilizationVariables(java.util.ArrayList<org.eclipse.uml2.uml.Element> resources,
                                                                 MILPModel2TextUtils milpGen)
        Generate variables for utilization constraints.

        For each resource instance, these variables are of the following form:
        ResourceInstanceID_busyTime = A(resInstRow,wp1)*wp1_opTime + ... for all working principles.

        Parameters:
        resources - A list of concrete resources
        milpGen - The MILP code generator.
        Returns:
        A list of variable definitions holding the busy time of each

      • computeAllCombinations

        private java.util.ArrayList<short[]> computeAllCombinations(short[] startingPoint)
        Computes the permutation of all binary strings computable by adding one from the given starting point.
        Parameters:
        startingPoint - Some binary number represented by an array acting as the starting point.
        Returns:
        A list of binary numbers represented by arrays of shorts that represent all possible combinations of 1s and 0s, starting from the starting point, incrementally adding "1" in each iteration.

        Parameters:

        Returns:
